 El Ni\u00f1o|periodical=Science|volume=288|issue=5468|pages=941\u2013942|pmid=10841705|doi=10.1126/science.288.5468.941a|url=http://www.scienceonline.org/cgi/content/summary/288/5468/941a|accessdate=5 April 2007}}\n* {{Citation|last=O'Hare |first=G.|year=1997|title=The Indian Monsoon, Part Two: The Rains|periodical=Geography|volume=82|issue=4|pages=335}}\n* {{Citation|last=Pant |first=G. B.|publication-date=2003|year=2003|title=Long-Term Climate Variability and Change over Monsoonal Asia|periodical=Journal of the Indian Geophysical Union|volume=7|issue=3|pages=125\u2013134|url=http://www.igu.in/7-3/2GBpant.pdf|accessdate=1 October 2011}}\n* {{Citation|last=Parthasarathy |first=B.|last2=Munot|first2=A. A.|last3=Kothawale|first3=D. R.|publication-date= December 1994|year=1994|title=All-India Monthly and Seasonal Rainfall Series: 1871\u20131993|periodical=Theoretical and Applied Climatology|volume=49|issue=4|pages=217\u2013224|issn=0177-798X|bibcode=1994ThApC..49..217P|doi=10.1007/BF00867461}}\n* {{Citation|last=Peterson |first=R. E.|last2=Mehta|first2=K. C.|publication-date=December 1981|year=1981|title=Climatology of Tornadoes of India and Bangladesh|periodical=Meteorology and Atmospheric Physics|volume=29|issue=4|pages=345\u2013356|doi=10.1007/bf02263310|bibcode=1981AMGBB..29..345P}}\n* {{Citation|last=Pisharoty |first=P. R.|last2=Desai|first2=B. N.|year=1956|title=Western Disturbances and Indian Weather|periodical=Indian Journal of Meteorological Geophysics|volume=7|pages=333\u2013338}}\n* {{Citation|last=Rowley |first=D. B.|publication-date=1996|year=1996|title=Age of Initiation of Collision Between India and Asia: A Review of Stratigraphic Data|periodical=Earth and Planetary Science Letters|volume=145|issue=1|pages=1\u201313|bibcode=1996E&PSL.145....1R|doi=10.1016/S0012-821X(96)00201-4|url=http://www.gps.caltech.edu/~avouac/GE277/Rowley96.pdf|accessdate=31 March 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061228205836/http://www.gps.caltech.edu/~avouac/GE277/R